==English==
===Pronunciation===
* [[IPA]]: /asfogəl/

===Etymology===
A direct loanword from the archaic Afrikaans ("aas" - Carrion; "vogel" - Bird), from the Dutch word.<br>
Note: The modern Afrikaans is "aasvoël".

===Noun===
'''aasvogel'''

# Any of a number of [[species]] of [[South African]] [[vulture]]
#:'''1912''': As the charge exploded I saw the '''aasvogel''' give a kind of backward twist. &mdash; ''Marie'', [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/H._Rider_Haggard H. Rider Haggard]

